# Aithos Protocol — licensing

This monorepo mixes **software** and **documentation** under different terms.

## Software (BSL 1.1 → Apache-2.0)

The following npm workspaces are licensed under the **Business Source License 1.1**
(**BUSL-1.1**):

- `packages/protocol-core` — `@aithos/protocol-core`
- `packages/cli` — `aithos`
- `packages/mcp` — `@aithos/mcp`

Each package ships a self-contained `LICENSE` file with the parameterized BSL text.

**Change Date:** 2030-12-31 (calendar year end).

**Change License:** Apache License, Version 2.0 — full text in this repository at
`LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt` and at https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.txt

**Important:** npm artifacts that were **published and distributed** under a
previous license (for example Apache-2.0) remain available under that license
for anyone who obtained those versions. Only **new releases** published under
BUSL-1.1 are governed by BUSL-1.1.

**Commercial licensing:** mathieucolla@gmail.com

## Documentation (CC BY 4.0)

Unless a file states otherwise, **normative and narrative documentation** in:

- `spec/`
- `SPEC.md`
- `WHITEPAPER.md`

is licensed under **Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International** (CC BY 4.0):
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode

This keeps the protocol specification readable and reusable independently of
the reference implementation’s commercial license.

## See also

- `ARCHITECTURE-DECISIONS.md` — ADR-0006 documents this stratification.
- https://mariadb.com/bsl11/ — Business Source License 1.1 FAQ.
